                    <span class="name bold font-m">Research Study</span>
                    <p class="description font-s">The choice of study type is a critical aspect of the design of medical studies to identify new therapies, drugs, and techniques. Study design, which covers planning, performance, documentation, analysis, and publication aspect of the study is also dependent on the study type which serves as an important determinant of selected studies quality and clinical value. 

When designing a study, please specify study category: <br/><br/>
(1) Basic Research - also known as experimental research that focuses on animal experiments, cell studies, biochemical, genetic, and physiological investigations on new drugs and therapies.<br/><br/>
(2) Clinical Research - includes experimental and observational studies on new drugs and therapies (i.e. Phase I - IV clinical studies).<br/><br/>
(3) Epidemiological research - investigation of the distribution and historical changes in disease frequency across various groups and geographies.</p>
